COPYRIGHT HOLDER: Scottish Government (Loch Rannoch shapefile)

Land Cover of Scotland Lochs

Land Cover of Scotland information was produced from aerial photography flown at 1:25,000 for the whole of Scotland by the Scottish Office (now Scottish Government) in 1988 and 1989.

Photographs were interpreted and processed by Macaulay Land Use Research Institute (now James Hutton Institute) and the digital dataset completed in 1993.

There are no licence restrictions for LCS data but printed maps should include the acknowledgement

‘Lochs from Land Cover of Scotland data, MLURI 1993’
OR
 ‘Lochs, LCS88, MLURI 1993’
